Comedian Tracy Morgan is still recovering from a 'traumatic' brain injury - more than five months after he was critically injured in a highway crash that killed one of his friends.

The 46-year-old was traveling back from a Delaware-based show in a limo van on June 7 when a 'speeding' Walmart truck slammed into the back of the vehicle on the New Jersey Turnpike.

He was rushed to hospital with serious injuries, including a broken leg, a broken nose and broken ribs. His friend and fellow comedian James McNair was killed, while three others were also injured. 

