Morgan, a former Saturday Night Live and 30 Rock star, was released from hospital on June 20, before undergoing several weeks of rehab for his injuries. He returned home on July 12. 

But more than five months on, the actor-comedian is still undergoing treatment for injuries to his brain, including daily speech, cognitive, vocational and physical therapies, it has emerged.

Lawyer Benedict Morelli revealed Morgan's long-lasting brain injury during a scheduling conference in the star's lawsuit against Walmart, in which he is suing for punitive and compensatory damages. 

On Tuesday, Morelli and other attorneys met in federal court to settle on a schedule for the lawsuit, which was filed in late September following the deadly crash. Morgan was not present. 

