The speed limit on that stretch of the New Jersey Turnpike is 55 mph and was lowered to 45 mph that night because of construction.

Earlier this year, New Jersey State Police Sgt. First Class Gregory Williams said Roper could have also been dozing off at the time because he 'failed to observe slow-moving traffic ahead.'

He said: 'He observed at the last minute -- just prior to impact -- the limo bus carrying Morgan and his party.' 

The case continues. 

 

 

